{"questionId":"29448794","questionHtml":"<p>Calculate the volume of the paperweight.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>units are required in part (a)(ii)</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{2} \\times \\frac{{4\\pi&nbsp; \\times {{\\left( 3 \\right)}^3}}}{3} + 3 \\times {\\left( 6 \\right)^2}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>4</mn>\n      <mi>π</mi>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>(</mo>\n              <mn>3</mn>\n              <mo>)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mn>6</mn>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for <strong>their</strong> correct substitution in volume of sphere formula divided by 2, <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for adding <strong>their</strong> correctly substituted volume of the cuboid.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>= 165 cm<sup>3&nbsp; &nbsp;</sup>(164.548…)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em><strong>(ft)</strong><em><strong> (C3)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> The answer is 165 cm<sup>3</sup>; the units are required. Follow through from part (a)(i).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"29448794","referenceCode":"18N.1.SL.TZ0.T_9a.ii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Calculate the volume of the paperweight.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["To